            <p>
              In our first meetings, we aimed to <strong>uncover Fabio Viviani Wines' goals for the redesign</strong>. We asked if they wanted to keep any of the existing site design, if they wanted to keep within the style guide they already had, what their brand values were, who their target audience was, and if there were any development constraints to consider.
              <br>
              <br>
              We learned <strong>they wanted a complete redesign</strong>, and that there was no accompanying UX research or design. Our clients sought to <strong>leverage Fabio's celebrity status</strong> and personality to build recognition, using the site to <strong>highlight how to pair the wines</strong>, ideally with Fabio's recipes. Their goal was to have the wines and the recipes coexist in order to turn users into frequent visitors.
              <br>
              <br>
              Before the redesign, their site audience was predominantly women in their mid-forties to mid-sixties; our clients wanted to lower the age of the visitors to those in their mid-twenties to early thirties. They asked us to create <strong>contemporary, accessible designs</strong> that felt rustic, authentic, and modern.
            </p>
