            <p>
              Ultimately, I was happy with the work I produced. It was difficult working without previous UX contributions, and I had to juggle the needs of UX while creating a visually pleasing language. That said, I found it incredibly rewarding to be able to dig into the UX while also working on the UI. It was fun to be able to create a site experience that was both beautiful and more user-friendly.
              <br>
              <br>
              I learned how to create navigations and flows that created an experience for users, and I gamified aspects of the site to encourage user involvement. I used my designs to solve problems I found in the existing site, including unclear navigation, haphazard hierarchy, lack of user guidance, and an overall static feeling site.
              <br>
              <br>
